Subject: Re: [T2] Please answer this question now. This is an urgent matter.

If you're discussing automatic transmissions, the rule is 25 mph Max, 25
Miles Max. Otherwise disconnect the drive shafts.
With standard trannys it can be as much as 100 mph at 45 mph. You can tow
much much farther if you disconnect the drive shafts.

Bill M.

